# Stage Routing

Every project built with this framework has 4 stages. Route each task to the correct stage doc.

## Stage map

| Stage | Folder | BOOT.md | When to use |
|-------|--------|---------|-------------|
| 0 — Discovery | `stages/00-discovery/` | `BOOT.md` | New project, defining goals, interview |
| 1 — Planning | `stages/01-planning/` | `BOOT.md` | Architecture, stack, roadmap |
| 2 — Build | `stages/02-build/` | `BOOT.md` | Active development, features |
| 3 — Deploy | `stages/03-deploy/` | `BOOT.md` | CI/CD, release, monitoring |

## How to route

1. Before starting a task, identify which stage it belongs to
2. Read that stage's `BOOT.md` with `@stages/XX-name/BOOT.md`
3. Follow the checklist and references inside BOOT.md
4. If stage is unclear → ask: "Это этап [N] или [N+1]?"

## Stage transition

- Do NOT move to next stage until current stage checklist is done
- On transition: update `HANDOFF.md`, `LAYER-3/project-status.md`, confirm with owner
- Deferred items → `LAYER-3/deferred-decisions.md`

## Cross-stage references

- Specs live in `LAYER-2/specs/` — always check before planning
- Decisions live in `LAYER-3/deferred-decisions.md` — read before architecture choices
- Lessons live in `LAYER-3/lessons.md` — read before repeating past mistakes
